ining loop where high-confidence predicted paths are used to refine IE and edge prediction components. GARP improves upon RAMS by replacing uncontrolled question generation with linguistically grounded reasoning motifs, reducing hallucination and enhancing reproducibility. It advances beyond Paper 1 by supporting incremental, online graph construction suitable for real-time dialogue, and surpasses Paper 2 by modeling generative reasoning as structured path discovery rather than passage co-selection. By anchoring multi-hop decisions in semantic roles and discourse logic, GARP ensures that each hop reflects a cognitively meaningful inference step, making it particularly effective in long, ambiguous dialogues where shallow heuristics fail.",
